nodes.output: The special election held in 2014 to replace Bill Young was won by David Jolly, a Republican, who defeated Democrat Alex Sink. This special election was held to fill the vacancy created by the death of U.S. Representative Bill Young.

nodes.instruction: Find out which candidates participated in the identified special election.
nodes.output:
The candidates who participated in the identified special elections are:

- Ed Neilson
- David Jolly
- Alex Sink
- Ed Markey
- Terry Tornek
- Emilio Vazquez
- Ron Henson (as the incumbent State Treasurer in the Louisiana State Treasurer special election)

nodes.instruction: Retrieve the election results for the special election.
nodes.output: The election results for the special election between David Jolly and Alex Sink on March 11, 2014, resulted in a victory for David Jolly, who won the race to fill the vacancy created by the death of U.S. Representative Bill Young. Jolly, a Republican, defeated Democrat Alex Sink in the special election.

nodes.instruction: Determine the winner of the election based on the results.
nodes.output: Based on the election results, the winner of the special election between David Jolly and Alex Sink on March 11, 2014, is David Jolly, a Republican. He defeated Democrat Alex Sink to fill the vacancy created by the death of U.S. Representative Bill Young. Therefore, David Jolly is the winner of the election.

Thomas Stephen Foley, KBE (March 6, 1929 – October 18, 2013) was an American lawyer and politician who served as the 49th Speaker of the United States House of Representatives from 1989 to 1995. Foley was the first Speaker of the House since 1862 to be defeated in a re-election campaign.
